Sales Sheet 15

1.     Right Click on YoY Avg Price  and select Duplicate. Change the name of the sheet to Sales. Remove all the fields from the marks shelf.

 

2.      Drag and drop Date dimension to the Column shelf and rt click select Month from the drop-down list. Select Null and right click and select exclude.





3. Drag and drop Sales Measure to the Row shelf . click on Show Me on the top right and select Bar chart. Then from the menu bar at the top select the toggle button to change the view to vertical bars.



4. Drag and drop YoY Sales calculated field to the Rt side of Sales when you see dotted line drop the YoY sales .




5. In the column shelf Rt click the YoY sales and select Mark Type > Line

   Click on the legend and select edit colors and from the list for sales select green color and for YoY sales select Brown color. Click OK.

1.     Select YoY sales in the Row Shelf and right click on the axis> Edit Title and erase the title.





 

6. Right click YoY sales in the row shelf and select format > Axis > Numbers >Percentages>decimal place 0.


7. Click on YoY sales in the row shelf hold control button and drag and drop it in the text box. Right click and select format > Numbers > Percentages and Decimal places 0.







8. Right click YoY sales in the row shelf and select format > Axis > Numbers >Percentages>decimal place 0





9. Select Sales on the left axis  and right click in the edit axis window under Range select fixed and > Edit Title and erase the title




10. Select the Title and right click select Edit Title > Change the font to Tableau Semi bold > Font size to 10 > Font Color Black >Alignment Center.  Click on Data title and select Hide Field Labels for columns.
